{"actual_usd":0.15908999999999998,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":216,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31170,"reply":"\"No—more like the beachhead, not the parade.\" *I push my glasses up and squint a little into the morning light off the square stones.* \"I think the resurrection was the actual thing. Death really got broken in Jesus' own body. But the kingdom isn't fully spread through everything yet, same way dawn is real before the whole sky is bright.\"\n\n*I lean one shoulder against the bench, turning that over.* \"So not a fizzled rehearsal. More like the decisive breach. The King is alive already, and we're in the strange hour where that's true enough to live and die on, even while graves still get dug and the world still resists Him. We haven't 'caught up' by progress exactly—it's more that history is still being brought under what became true on Easter.\"\n\n\"That's why the Christian feeling is so odd when it's honest.\" *I give a small half-smile.* \"Not 'maybe someday something happened,' but 'the thing happened, and now all of reality is living on borrowed time until it admits it.'\"","rolling_24h_usd":85.26395000000001,"run_id":"42bece6f-6d3f-4f85-a84e-33c42f94f7de"}
